## Spring Ecosystem Announces First Release Candidates for Major Updates (October 20, 2025)

The Spring ecosystem experienced significant activity during the week of October 20th, 2025, with the release of first release candidates for numerous projects. These candidates represent key milestones in the development cycle and introduce new features, improvements, and bug fixes. This summary details the notable updates across various Spring projects.

### Overview

A total of nine Spring projects released their first release candidates: Spring Boot, Spring Security, Spring for GraphQL, Spring Session, Spring Integration, Spring Modulith, Spring REST Docs, Spring Batch, and Spring AMQP.  These releases primarily focus on bug fixes, dependency upgrades, and the introduction of new functionalities.

### Project-Specific Updates

#### Spring Boot 4.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 4.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Support for the new Spring Framework `RestTestClient` interface.
    *   Modularization of the codebase to reduce application size and improve auto-configuration.
*   **Details:**  The modularization aims to provide stronger auto-configuration signals, simplifying application setup.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/) (Note: URL is a placeholder as the full URL wasn't provided in the context)

#### Spring Security 7.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 7.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   New `@EnableGlobalMultiFactorAuthentication` annotation for exposing a multi-factor authentication bean.
    *   `DefaultAuthorizationManagerFactory` class for managing authority granted to `FactorGrantedAuthority` instances.
*   **Details:** These additions enhance the flexibility and management of multi-factor authentication within Spring Security.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring for GraphQL 2.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 2.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Kotlin extensions for the `GraphQlClient` and interfaces.
    *   `GraphQlTester` class for copying HTTP headers into a `HttpRequestHeaderInterceptor` instance.
*   **Details:**  These features improve the testing and integration of GraphQL APIs within Spring applications.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring Session 4.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 4.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Modernization of Antora documentation site generation builds.
    *   Addition of exclusions to the `nohttp` Gradle plugin.
*   **Details:** These updates focus on improving documentation generation and build processes.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring Integration 7.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 7.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   New channel adapters based on Spring AMQP 4.0.
    *   Runtime configuration of the `FileReadingMessageSource` class.
*   **Details:**  The new channel adapters and runtime configuration enhance the flexibility and extensibility of Spring Integration.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring Modulith 2.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 2.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Removal of the deprecated `@ApplicationEventListener` annotation.
    *   Support for executing Flyway database migrations on startup.
*   **Details:** These changes streamline application development and simplify database migration management.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring REST Docs 4.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 4.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Alignment with JUnit 6.0 as the minimal supported version.
    *   Temporary drop in support for REST-Assured.
*   **Details:**  The update to JUnit 6.0 ensures compatibility with the latest testing frameworks.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring Batch 6.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 6.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Graceful shutdown of batch jobs.
    *   Support for Staged Event Driven Architecture (SEDA) processing.
*   **Details:** These features improve the reliability and scalability of batch processing applications.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring AMQP 4.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 4.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Resolution of an issue with the `allowEagerInit` parameter in `getBeansOfType`.
*   **Details:** This resolves a bug that caused eager instantiation of beans, breaking lazy initialization semantics.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring for Apache Kafka 4.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 4.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Concurrency support for `ShareKafkaMessageListenerContainer`.
    *   Change to the constructor signature of `KafkaOperations` to accept `DeadLetterPublishingRecoverer`.
*   **Details:** These additions enhance the performance and resilience of Kafka integration.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring for Apache Pulsar 2.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 2.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Resolution of the `deadLetterTopic` attribute issue.
*   **Details:** This ensures proper handling of dead messages in Apache Pulsar.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring Web Services 5.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 5.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Alignment JUnit 6.0 as the minimal supported version.
*   **Details:** Ensures compatibility with the latest JUnit version.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)

#### Spring Vault 4.0.0

*   **Release Candidate:** 4.0.0
*   **Key Features:**
    *   Dependency upgrades (JDK 25, Spring Framework 7.0.0, Spring Data 2025.1.0, JUnit 6.0, Jackson 3.0).
    *   Support for Spring Framework `RestClient` interface.
*   **Details:**  These upgrades enhance security and functionality.
*   **Reference:** [Release Notes](https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/10/spring-news-roundup-oct20-2025/)